description:
T2 - Norway maple - See site plan for location - Touching street lamp - Would like to prune to give 2m clearance
T4 - Common Oak - See site plan for location - Major deadwood and crown die back - Would like to remove deadwood / reduce back to live growth. Re-shape to form natural shaped crown
T11 - Norway maple - See site plan for location - Touching building - Would like to prune to give 2m clearance
T15 - Sycamore - See site plan for location - Poor joint between main trunk and sub trunk - Would like to reduce sub trunk by 3 metres in heigh
T18 - Ash - See site plan for location - Deadwood - Would like to remove major deadwood.
T30  - Sycamore - See site plan for location - Old pruning wound resulting in large cavity at 2.5m - Would like to reduce height of tree by 5m
T40  - Sycamore - See site plan for location - Hollow between 3 and 6 metres - Would like to crown reduce by 4 metres
T53 - Narrow-leaved Ash - See site plan for location - Historical limb loss, healing normally. Touching building. Recently crown reduced - Would like to prune to give 2 metres clearance to building.
T54 - Narrow-leaved Ash - See site plan for location - Touching building - Would like to prune to give 2m clearance to building.
T58 - Narrow-leaved Ash - See site plan for location - Suspended branches within crown - Would like to clear broken / suspended branches
T59 - Rowan - See site plan for location - Deadwood - Would like to remove deadwood.
T60 - Deodar Cedar - See site plan for location - Split in limb (near old pruning wound), over pavement south side at 5 m. Large pruning wound at ground level. Appears stable - Would like to reduce upwards growing section of limb by 4 m (lower section of limb only)
T68  - Sweet Chestnut - See site plan for location - Showing signs of post-development stress in upper crown. Limb loss at 2 metres. Appears stable. Touching building - Would like to prune to give 2 metre clearance to building
